            <strong>üá¶üá™ UAE hedge funds struggle</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hedge fund managers in Dubai and Abu Dhabi face a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-08-03-2025-wn1-3-challenging-work-environment" target="_blank">challenging work environment</a> despite the region‚Äôs booming finance sector. While Dubai is launching a hedge fund hub and Abu Dhabi has a dedicated ‚Äúhedge fund island,‚Äù job security remains low, with a hire-and-fire culture. Some funds, including Brevan Howard, have already cut staff.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Rising living costs and short jobseeker visas add to the challenges. Experts advise securing long-term contracts or golden visas before relocating. The UAE‚Äôs finance industry is growing, but job uncertainty and high expenses make it a risky move for professionals.</p>
