          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
            Since Trump's election, European equities have outperformed US stocks, attracting investor interest and significant fund inflows. In the first week of March, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-08-03-2025-wn3-5-4-billion-flowed-into-western-european-equity" target="_blank">$4 Bn flowed into Western European equity</a> funds, marking the largest inflow in three years. Analysts at Barclays suggest this surge is a relief rally, but Germany‚Äôs fiscal stimulus, including a $550 Bn infrastructure fund, could signal a long-term shift. 
            </p>
